latestIgtvVideos.title: Kudi Nu Nachne De ft. @yashasvirathi @namrata.pant.773 @mansisharma492
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
@apurvanand12 @mahakpareek @ruchisatwani.

For this blog I contacted my girl friends to make a video on current #trendingsong “Kudi Nu Nachne De” from @angrezi_medium_movie .The purpose was to give them wings and feel the amazing lyrics by @priyasaraiyaofficial

Here is why?

Have you ever felt conscious taking photos?

Or afraid of public opinions, comments or laughter whether you are content creator or anything.

Have you confined yourself just because you think that people will find you dumb?And you never started something for yourself or did what you wanted to for so long.

Even I was feeling the same insecurity before blooming my idea of blogging. But I started anyway.

Let’s discuss the depth. We need to understand few things:

That we have the same freedom as others, to make our own choices and have the opportunity for choice without any restraints or judgment.

To feel confident in yourself, your beliefs and your values. If you don’t believe in yourself then why would anyone be.

To move beyond labels and to know what you’re doing is right for yourself.

What do you think that people will think of you? That is bothering you. -She is dumb
-She has a weird nose
-She has zero conversation skills
-Who does she think she is, an influencer?!
-That’s a weird outfit/pointless pose

Let me remind you, regardless of social presence we do take pictures, create content or do something funny, that’s a part of our lifestyle.

So what can be the worst case, is that someone just finds you not so interesting and they won't contact you ever again. Would that really matter to you?

But you will eventually get used to it and create content, or shoot pictures or videos for yourself or your business. Sounds like a pretty good trade to me.

Don’t forget to think positive, not everyone thinks like that. There are people who will appreciate you for your work because not everyone has the courage to break the bars. Here your journey begins girl!
